                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1344" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1344" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1344" type="surname" value="ELLIOTT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1344" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH ELLIOTT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am housekeeper to Mr. Cubitt, at Clapham, he is a customer to Mr. Terry, the butcher. I know the prisoner—Mr. Cubitt had his bills weekly—the prisoner used to bring them, and I paid him a week after—when the bills were paid, they were delivered to him to get receipted by his master, and bring back again—the prisoner put "paid" himself to this bill of 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—the date of the last item is the 19th of August—I paid it the prisoner on the 22nd—on the 12th of September I paid the prisoner two bills of 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 16<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. and 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., making in the whole 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 8<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I gave him the bills to get receipted—I asked him for them—he said it was all right, and he would bring the 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. change—the next morning I had some suspicion, and inquired of Mr. Terry the next day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I paid the 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. to my master.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183709180206"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1345" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1345" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1345" type="surname" value="TERRY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1345" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM TERRY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a butcher, at Clapham. The prisoner was in my service—he was in the habit of receiving money on my account—✗ was always a rule laid down to him, to take the money and bring the bills to me, or his mistress to write the receipt, and take them back—it was his duty to pay me the money—Mr. Cubitt was a customer—the prisoner did not account to me for 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., paid on the 10th of August—he paid the sum of 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 8<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. after I challenged him with it in my own house, he gave me two sovereigns, two half-crowns, and two sixpences, and I found the bills in his cart.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. The 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. I spent—I paid away some money to my club.</p>
